HEADWORD: Homographic
<hw>Ho`mo*graph"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Employing a single and separate character to represent each sound;
-- said of certain methods of spelling words.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Geom.)</fld> <def>Possessing the property of
homography.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Homography</ent>⟦br⟧
